24/02/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Six miners were killed and at least eight others were injured in a methane explosion in a bitumen mine, Industry Minister Viktor Doda said Monday (23 February).
NATO helicopters were used to transport some of the injured to Greece and Italy.
France's KLP Industries operates the mine in Selenice, where the blast occurred.
The company denied reports by miners that safety standards had not been implemented properly.
The government has launched an investigation into the incident.
Prime Minister Fatos Nano pledged those responsible for the tragedy would be punished.
Two company officials reportedly were arrested.
(Albanian Daily News - 24/02/04;
Reuters, AFP, ATA - 23/02/04)
